Canada Regulators Plan New Rules on High-Speed Trading, National Post Says

-- B y   K e v i n   B e l l
-- 
2011-04-08T11:34:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/canada-regulators-plan-new-rules-on-high-speed-trading-national-post-says.html
Canadian regulators are planning to
take the first steps towards introducing new rules on high-speed
electronic trading, perhaps as early as today, the National Post
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the plans.  Regulators also plan stricter monitoring of direct market
access to exchanges, known as “unfiltered” or “naked
access,” the Post reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Bell at 
 kbell2@bloomberg.net  